egime, the non-monotonic HPs of the second DLL induce two-particle\ncorrelations which are reminiscent of paired states such as the Haffnian state.\nVia exact diagonalization in the disk geometry, we compute experimentally\nrelevant observables such as density profiles and correlations, and we study\nthe entanglement spectra as a further tool to characterize the obtained\nstrongly correlated states.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Nov 2014 18:03:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 9 Mar 2015 14:48:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-10"}
