infer that the TiO line\nlist poorly match the real positions of TiO lines at spectral resolutions of\n~100,000. Similar line lists are also used in the PHOENIX and Kurucz stellar\natmosphere suites and we show that their synthetic M-dwarf spectra also\ncorrelate poorly with the HARPS spectra of Barnard's star and five other\nM-dwarfs. We conclude that the lack of an accurate TiO line list is currently\ncritically hampering this high-resolution retrieval technique.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Nov 2014 21:03:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-02-18"}
